\pi\cdot2\cdot50=100\pi {\text{ cm}\over\text{rev}}
\def\textstyle{} 25{\textstyle {\text{ rev} \over \text{ min}}}\cdot\textstyle{1\over 60}\textstyle{\text{min}\over \text{sec}  }  ={25\over 60}{\text{rev}\over\text{sec}} ={5\over12}{\text{rev}\over\text{sec}}.
\underbrace{100\pi \textstyle {\text{ cm}\over\text{rev}}}_{\text{ dist per rev}}\cdot\underbrace{\textstyle {5\over12}\textstyle{\text{rev}\over\text{sec}}\cdot 1\text{sec}}_{ \text{number of revs.}}={125\pi\over3} \text{ cm}.
